<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-07-05T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-07-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="841" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d841">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">821.51/2525</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Colombia</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Braden</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 843</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Bogotá</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-07-05">July 5, 1940</date>.<lb/>[Received July
                                12.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to inform the Department
                            that by Decree 1036 of May 30, 1940, the Government of Colombia
                            guarantees such obligations as the Bank of the Republic may contract
                            from the Export-Import Bank under the maximum $10,000,000 line of credit
                            extended to that organization. The Ministry of Finance and Public Credit
                            is authorized to sign on behalf of the Nation so as to make this
                            guarantee of record. Copy of the original text, together with
                            translation, of the aforementioned decree are enclosed herewith.<note n="10" xml:id="d841fn1">Not printed.</note></p>
                        <p>Respectfully yours,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Spruille Braden</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>